&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outer £57,990 - £66,823 pa inc. HCA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;JOB REF: 312- CPH- 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Be Part of Our Team...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of our ongoing service development, the Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust have a new and exciting role to establish the new Staff Psychology service. This is an excellent opportunity to take forward the considerable investment being made and to develop the new service and provide targeted support to individual staff members and teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced Clinical Psychologist to join our team. You will be a key member of the multi- disciplinary team working in collaboration with the Consultant Psychologist lead to provide the Staff Psychology Service that forms part of the Trust’s Wellbeing provision within Occupational Health that is helping to deliver support for all Staff at the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the new service, you would be providing assessment, case management and evidence-based interventions. With targeted support, guidance and consultation to individual staff members and teams. There will be opportunity for professional development and innovation, and you will have scope and support to develop your own practice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 9th &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;November 2020 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will take place w/c 19th &lt;strong&gt;November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;We reserve the right to expire vacancies prior to the advertised closing date if a sufficient number of applications have been received. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;To discuss the post or If you would like more information please contact Jon Head, Deputy Director Human Resources &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;J.Head2@rbht.nhs.uk &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or on mobile number 07880 791667&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
